name: BULBASAUR
entries: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower’s coming bloom.

name: IVYSAUR
entries: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

name: VENUSAUR
entries: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

name: CHARMANDER
entries: In the rocky mountains where CHARMELEON live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

name: CHARMELEON
entries: It is said that CHARIZARD’s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

name: CHARIZARD
entries: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

name: SQUIRTLE
entries: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

name: WARTORTLE
entries: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

name: BLASTOISE
entries: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.

name: CATERPIE
entries: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

name: METAPOD
entries: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

name: BUTTERFREE
entries: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.

name: WEEDLE
entries: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: KAKUNA
entries: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.

name: BEEDRILL
entries: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: PIDGEY
entries: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

name: PIDGEOTTO
entries: By flapping its wings with all its might, PIDGEOT can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.

name: PIDGEOT
entries: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.

name: RATTATA
entries: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.

name: RATICATE
entries: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

name: SPEAROW
entries: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

name: FEAROW
entries: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

name: EKANS
entries: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

name: ARBOK
entries: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.

name: PIKACHU
entries: It turns aggressive if it has too much electricity in its body. It discharges power through its tail.

name: RAICHU
entries: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.

name: SANDSHREW
entries: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.

name: SANDSLASH
entries: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from barbs can be fatal.

name: NIDORANfE
entries: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than NIDORINO’s.

name: NIDORINA
entries: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.

name: NIDOQUEEN
entries: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

name: NIDORANmA
entries: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

name: NIDORINO
entries: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

name: NIDOKING
entries: Thought to live with others on quiet mountains, it is popular for its adorable nature.

name: CLEFAIRY
entries: Rarely seen by people, it is said to be drawn by the full moon to play at deserted lakes.

name: CLEFABLE
entries: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.

name: VULPIX
entries: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.

name: NINETALES
entries: When it wavers its big, round eyes, it begins singing a lullaby that makes everyone drowsy.

name: JIGGLYPUFF
entries: Its fine fur feels sublime to the touch. It can expand its body by inhaling air.

name: WIGGLYTUFF
entries: Even though it has no eyes, it can sense obstacles using ultrasonic waves it emits from its mouth.

name: ZUBAT
entries: It loves the blood of humans and Pokémon. It flies around at night in search of neck veins.

name: GOLBAT
entries: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

name: ODDISH
entries: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

name: GLOOM
entries: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

name: VILEPLUME
entries: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host PARAS.

name: PARAS
entries: A mushroom grown larger than the host’s body controls PARASECT. It scatters poisonous spores.

name: PARASECT
entries: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

name: VENONAT
entries: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

name: VENOMOTH
entries: A Pokémon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

name: DIGLETT
entries: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

name: DUGTRIO
entries: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

name: MEOWTH
entries: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

name: PERSIAN
entries: If its usual headache worsens, it starts exhibiting odd powers. It can’t remember doing so, however.

name: PSYDUCK
entries: A Pokémon that lives in lakes. It swims faster than any human swimming champion.

name: GOLDUCK
entries: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

name: MANKEY
entries: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

name: PRIMEAPE
entries: A Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

name: GROWLITHE
entries: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.

name: ARCANINE
entries: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

name: POLIWAG
entries: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

name: POLIWHIRL
entries: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

name: POLIWRATH
entries: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. Even when awake, it teleports itself while remaining seated.

name: ABRA
entries: If one is nearby, an eerie shadow appears on TV screens. Seeing the shadow is said to bring bad luck.

name: KADABRA
entries: Its superb memory lets it recall everything it has experienced from birth. Its IQ exceeds 5,000.

name: ALAKAZAM
entries: It hefts a GRAVELER repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.

name: MACHOP
entries: MACHOKE’s boundless power is very dangerous, so it wears a belt that suppresses its energy.

name: MACHOKE
entries: It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1,000 punches in two seconds.

name: MACHAMP
entries: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

name: BELLSPROUT
entries: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

name: WEEPINBELL
entries: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

name: VICTREEBEL
entries: Its body is virtually composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

name: TENTACOOL
entries: With 80 tentacles for ensnaring victims, it prevents escape until the prey is weakened by poison.

name: TENTACRUEL
entries: Many live on mountain trails and remain half buried while keeping an eye on climbers.

name: GEODUDE
entries: GRAVELER make their homes on sheer cliff faces by gouging out numerous horizontal holes.

name: GRAVELER
entries: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulderlike body is so tough, even dynamite can’t harm it.

name: GOLEM
entries: About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.

name: PONYTA
entries: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

name: RAPIDASH
entries: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

name: SLOWPOKE
entries: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the SHELLDER on its tail bites down.

name: SLOWBRO
entries: The units at its sides generate electromagnetic waves that keep it airborne. It feeds on electricity.

name: MAGNEMITE
entries: It is actually three MAGNEMITE linked by magnetism. A group can set off a magnetic storm.

name: MAGNETON
entries: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

name: FARFETCH'D
entries: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

name: DODUO
entries: When DODUO evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.

name: DODRIO
entries: A Pokémon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.

name: SEEL
entries: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.

name: DEWGONG
entries: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon’s X-rays. It appears among filth.

name: GRIMER
entries: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

name: MUK
entries: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

name: SHELLDER
entries: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

name: CLOYSTER
entries: This Pokémon’s body is 95% made up of gases, which are blown away by strong gusts of wind.

name: GASTLY
entries: It can slip through any obstacle. It lurks inside walls to keep an eye on its foes.

name: HAUNTER
entries: It hides in shadows. It is said that if GENGAR is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees F.

name: GENGAR
entries: When it travels underground, it causes rumbling and tremors. It can move at 50 mph.

name: ONIX
entries: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

name: DROWZEE
entries: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

name: HYPNO
entries: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

name: KRABBY
entries: The larger pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

name: KINGLER
entries: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

name: VOLTORB
entries: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

name: ELECTRODE
entries: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

name: EXEGGCUTE
entries: It is called “The Walking Jungle.” If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an EXEGGCUTE.

name: EXEGGUTOR
entries: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

name: CUBONE
entries: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

name: MAROWAK
entries: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

name: HITMONLEE
entries: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

name: HITMONCHAN
entries: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.

name: LICKITUNG
entries: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.

name: KOFFING
entries: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.

name: WEEZING
entries: Its body is clad in a thick hide, and its tackles topple buildings. Unfortunately, it is not smart.

name: RHYHORN
entries: Its brain developed after it stood up on its hind legs. Its drill horn bores tunnels through solid rock.

name: RHYDON
entries: It is said to deliver happiness. Being compassionate, it shares its eggs with injured people.

name: CHANSEY
entries: It is shrouded by blue vines. No one has seen the face hidden behind this growth of vines.

name: TANGELA
entries: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

name: KANGASKHAN
entries: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

name: HORSEA
entries: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.

name: SEADRA
entries: It swims elegantly by flittering its tail fin as if it were a dress. It has the look of a queen.

name: GOLDEEN
entries: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. It defends its eggs with its life.

name: SEAKING
entries: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

name: STARYU
entries: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

name: STARMIE
entries: It is a pantomime expert that can create invisible but solid walls using miming gestures.

name: MR. MIME
entries: It is nearly impossible to parry its attacking scythes. Its movements are like a ninja’s.

name: SCYTHER
entries: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

name: JYNX
entries: Half of all blackouts occur when this Pokémon appears at power plants and eats electricity.

name: ELECTABUZZ
entries: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.

name: MAGMAR
entries: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can’t tear, it tosses far.

name: PINSIR
entries: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

name: TAUROS
entries: It is said to be the world’s weakest Pokémon. No one knows why it has managed to survive.

name: MAGIKARP
entries: Once it appears, its rage never settles until it has razed the fields and mountains around it.

name: GYARADOS
entries: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.

name: LAPRAS
entries: It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.

name: DITTO
entries: A rare Pokémon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.

name: EEVEE
entries: It has evolved to be suitable for an aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.

name: VAPOREON
entries: It controls 10,000-volt power and can raise all the fur on its body as if it were sharp needles.

name: JOLTEON
entries: It has a flame sac in its body. Its body temperature tops 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit before battle.

name: FLAREON
entries: The world’s first artificially created Pokémon. It can travel through electronic space.

name: PORYGON
entries: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.

name: OMANYTE
entries: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.

name: OMASTAR
entries: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

name: KABUTO
entries: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

name: KABUTOPS
entries: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

name: AERODACTYL
entries: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.

name: SNORLAX
entries: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

name: ARTICUNO
entries: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

name: ZAPDOS
entries: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

name: MOLTRES
entries: It is called the “Mirage Pokémon” because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

name: DRATINI
entries: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

name: DRAGONAIR
entries: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

name: DRAGONITE
entries: A Pokémon created by recombining MEW’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: MEWTWO
entries: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe MEW to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

name: MEW
entries: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

name: CHIKORITA
entries: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

name: BAYLEEF
entries: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.

name: MEGANIUM
entries: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

name: CYNDAQUIL
entries: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.

name: QUILAVA
entries: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.

name: TYPHLOSION
entries: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

name: TOTODILE
entries: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

name: CROCONAW
entries: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

name: FERALIGATR
entries: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.

name: SENTRET
entries: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

name: FURRET
entries: It always stands on one foot. Even when attacked, it does not brace itself using both feet.

name: HOOTHOOT
entries: Its eyes are special. They can pick out objects as long as there is the tiniest amount of light.

name: NOCTOWL
entries: It is so timid, it can’t move if it isn’t with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

name: LEDYBA
entries: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

name: LEDIAN
entries: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

name: SPINARAK
entries: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

name: ARIADOS
entries: Having four wings enables it to fly faster and more quietly. It turns active when the night comes.

name: CROBAT
entries: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

name: CHINCHOU
entries: LANTURN’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed “The Deep-Sea Star.”

name: LANTURN
entries: The electric pouches on its cheeks are still small. They cannot store much electricity yet.

name: PICHU
entries: Its silhouette is like a star. It is believed to arrive riding on shooting stars.

name: CLEFFA
entries: It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.

name: IGGLYBUFF
entries: Its shell is said to be stuffed with happiness that it shares with kindhearted people.

name: TOGEPI
entries: It is said to appear in front of kindly people to scatter a glowing down called “joy dust.”

name: TOGETIC
entries: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

name: NATU
entries: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

name: XATU
entries: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

name: MAREEP
entries: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

name: FLAAFFY
entries: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail’s light.

name: AMPHAROS
entries: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

name: BELLOSSOM
entries: Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow on river bottoms.

name: MARILL
entries: It lives in rivers and lakes. In water, its coloring and patterns trick the vision of foes.

name: AZUMARILL
entries: Despite appearing to be a tree, its body is closer to rocks and stones. It is very weak to water.

name: SUDOWOODO
entries: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make POLIWAG obey.

name: POLITOED
entries: It drifts on winds. It is said that when HOPPIP gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: HOPPIP
entries: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

name: SKIPLOOM
entries: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

name: JUMPLUFF
entries: It uses its tail to pluck fruits that are out of reach. Its tail is more adept than its real hands.

name: AIPOM
entries: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.

name: SUNKERN
entries: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

name: SUNFLORA
entries: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won’t miss prey--even those behind it.

name: YANMA
entries: It lives in cold water, half burying itself in mud at the bottom to sleep.

name: WOOPER
entries: It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river’s bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.

name: QUAGSIRE
entries: Its fur has the look and feel of velvet. The orb on its forehead glows when it uses psycho-power.

name: ESPEON
entries: The light of the moon changed EEVEE’s genetic structure. It lurks in darkness for prey.

name: UMBREON
entries: It is believed that seeing this Pokémon at night will bring about ominous occurrences.

name: MURKROW
entries: Being bitten by SHELLDER gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

name: SLOWKING
entries: It loves to sneak up on people late at night, then startle them with its shrieklike cry.

name: MISDREAVUS
entries: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: UNOWN
entries: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

name: WOBBUFFET
entries: Its tail also has a small brain. It bites to repel any foe trying to sneak up on it from behind.

name: GIRAFARIG
entries: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

name: PINECO
entries: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

name: FORRETRESS
entries: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

name: DUNSPARCE
entries: It sails on the winds with its limbs extended to strike from the sky. It aims for the prey’s face.

name: GLIGAR
entries: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.

name: STEELIX
entries: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

name: SNUBBULL
entries: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

name: GRANBULL
entries: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

name: QWILFISH
entries: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

name: SCIZOR
entries: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.

name: SHUCKLE
entries: It gathers in forests to search for tree sap, its favorite food. It’s strong enough to hurl foes.

name: HERACROSS
entries: It feeds on eggs stolen from nests. Its sharply hooked claws rip vulnerable spots on prey.

name: SNEASEL
entries: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

name: TEDDIURSA
entries: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

name: URSARING
entries: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

name: SLUGMA
entries: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

name: MAGCARGO
entries: It loves eating mushrooms that grow under dead grass. It also finds hot springs while foraging.

name: SWINUB
entries: Its shaggy coat makes it unable to see. It checks surroundings with its sensitive nose instead.

name: PILOSWINE
entries: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

name: CORSOLA
entries: It squirts water forcefully from its mouth to shoot down flying prey.

name: REMORAID
entries: It lives in the gaps of boulders and in holes on the seafloor. Its suction cups grip prey tightly.

name: OCTILLERY
entries: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

name: DELIBIRD
entries: When the waves are calm, one may encounter a swarm of MANTINE swimming as if they are in flight.

name: MANTINE
entries: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph.

name: SKARMORY
entries: It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.

name: HOUNDOUR
entries: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

name: HOUNDOOM
entries: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

name: KINGDRA
entries: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

name: PHANPY
entries: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

name: DONPHAN
entries: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

name: PORYGON2
entries: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

name: STANTLER
entries: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

name: SMEARGLE
entries: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

name: TYROGUE
entries: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.

name: HITMONTOP
entries: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

name: SMOOCHUM
entries: It generates electricity by whirling its arms. However, it can’t store the energy it makes.

name: ELEKID
entries: Its body temperature is around 1,100 degrees F. It is healthy if it is breathing yellow flames.

name: MAGBY
entries: It is said that kids who drink MILTANK’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

name: MILTANK
entries: This kindhearted Pokémon nurses sick Pokémon to health. It senses feelings of sadness.

name: BLISSEY
entries: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

name: RAIKOU
entries: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: ENTEI
entries: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

name: SUICUNE
entries: A Pokémon that eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.

name: LARVITAR
entries: Its body is as hard as bedrock. By venting pressurized gas, it can launch itself like a rocket.

name: PUPITAR
entries: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

name: TYRANITAR
entries: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

name: LUGIA
entries: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

name: HO-OH
entries: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

name: CELEBI
entries: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

name: TREECKO
entries: It lives in dense jungles. While  closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

name: GROVYLE
entries: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

name: SCEPTILE
entries: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

name: TORCHIC
entries: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

name: COMBUSKEN
entries: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

name: BLAZIKEN
entries: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

name: MUDKIP
entries: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

name: MARSHTOMP
entries: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

name: SWAMPERT
entries: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: POOCHYENA
entries: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.

name: MIGHTYENA
entries: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

name: ZIGZAGOON
entries: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

name: LINOONE
entries: It loves to eat leaves. If it is attacked by a STARLY, it will defend itself with its spiked rear.

name: WURMPLE
entries: It anchors itself by wrapping twigs with the silk from its body. It motionlessly awaits evolution.

name: SILCOON
entries: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey’s fluids.

name: BEAUTIFLY
entries: It is hot inside its cocoon. All the cells in its body create the energy for it to evolve.

name: CASCOON
entries: A nocturnal Pokémon. Drawn by streetlights, they messily eat the leaves of trees lining boulevards.

name: DUSTOX
entries: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can’t swim.

name: LOTAD
entries: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

name: LOMBRE
entries: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.

name: LUDICOLO
entries: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

name: SEEDOT
entries: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

name: NUZLEAF
entries: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.

name: SHIFTRY
entries: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

name: TAILLOW
entries: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dives steeply to catch the prey.

name: SWELLOW
entries: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

name: WINGULL
entries: It dips its large bill in the sea, then scoops up numerous prey along with water.

name: PELIPPER
entries: It uses the horns on its head to sense human emotions. It is said to appear in front of cheerful people.

name: RALTS
entries: It is highly perceptive of its Trainer’s feelings. It dances when it is feeling happy.

name: KIRLIA
entries: It will try to guard its trusted Trainer with its life. It has the ability to see the future.

name: GARDEVOIR
entries: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

name: SURSKIT
entries: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

name: MASQUERAIN
entries: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

name: SHROOMISH
entries: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

name: BRELOOM
entries: It spends nearly all its time in a day sprawled out. Just seeing it makes one drowsy.

name: SLAKOTH
entries: Its heart beats at a tenfold tempo, so it cannot sit still for even a moment.

name: VIGOROTH
entries: The world’s laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.

name: SLAKING
entries: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

name: NINCADA
entries: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

name: NINJASK
entries: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

name: SHEDINJA
entries: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

name: WHISMUR
entries: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

name: LOUDRED
entries: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.

name: EXPLOUD
entries: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

name: MAKUHITA
entries: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

name: HARIYAMA
entries: A Pokémon that lives by water. It moves quickly on land by bouncing on its big tail.

name: AZURILL
entries: Its nose is a magnet. As a result, this Pokémon always keeps its face pointing north.

name: NOSEPASS
entries: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

name: SKITTY
entries: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

name: DELCATTY
entries: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

name: SABLEYE
entries: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

name: MAWILE
entries: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.

name: ARON
entries: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.

name: LAIRON
entries: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.

name: AGGRON
entries: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

name: MEDITITE
entries: Through yoga training, it has honed its sixth sense. Its movements are elegant.

name: MEDICHAM
entries: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

name: ELECTRIKE
entries: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

name: MANECTRIC
entries: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

name: PLUSLE
entries: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

name: MINUN
entries: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves ILLUMISE’s sweet aroma.

name: VOLBEAT
entries: With its sweet aroma, it guides VOLBEAT to draw signs with light in the night sky.

name: ILLUMISE
entries: ROSELIA raised on clean drinking water are known to grow vividly colored flowers.

name: ROSELIA
entries: Almost all its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.

name: GULPIN
entries: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

name: SWALOT
entries: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

name: CARVANHA
entries: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as “The Bully of the Sea.”

name: SHARPEDO
entries: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.

name: WAILMER
entries: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

name: WAILORD
entries: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.

name: NUMEL
entries: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.

name: CAMERUPT
entries: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

name: TORKOAL
entries: It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.

name: SPOINK
entries: It uses black pearls to amplify its psycho-power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

name: GRUMPIG
entries: No two SPINDA have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.

name: SPINDA
entries: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

name: TRAPINCH
entries: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.

name: VIBRAVA
entries: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as “The Desert Spirit.”

name: FLYGON
entries: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive for 30 days without water.

name: CACNEA
entries: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day’s desert heat.

name: CACTURNE
entries: Its wings are like cotton tufts. If it perches on someone’s head, it looks like a cotton hat.

name: SWABLU
entries: It looks like a fluffy cloud when it is in flight. It hums with its soprano voice.

name: ALTARIA
entries: It has feuded with SEVIPER for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.

name: ZANGOOSE
entries: For many generations, it has feuded with ZANGOOSE. It whets its bladed tail on rocks for battle.

name: SEVIPER
entries: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

name: LUNATONE
entries: A new Pokémon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.

name: SOLROCK
entries: It coats its entire body with a slimy fluid so it can squirm and slip away if grabbed.

name: BARBOACH
entries: It is very territorial. It repels foes by setting off tremors that extend over a three-mile radius.

name: WHISCASH
entries: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

name: CORPHISH
entries: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.

name: CRAWDAUNT
entries: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

name: BALTOY
entries: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.

name: CLAYDOL
entries: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

name: LILEEP
entries: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

name: CRADILY
entries: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.

name: ANORITH
entries: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.

name: ARMALDO
entries: It is famous for its shabby appearance. While populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.

name: FEEBAS
entries: When people bicker, it is said to arise from the depths of lakes to becalm violent hearts.

name: MILOTIC
entries: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

name: CASTFORM
entries: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.

name: KECLEON
entries: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

name: SHUPPET
entries: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.

name: BANETTE
entries: It doggedly pursues its prey wherever it goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.

name: DUSKULL
entries: Its body is hollow. It is said that those who look into its body are sucked into the void.

name: DUSCLOPS
entries: Because it continually ate only its favorite fruit, the fruit started growing around its neck.

name: TROPIUS
entries: To knock foes flying, it makes the air shudder with its cries. It converses using seven cries.

name: CHIMECHO
entries: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.

name: ABSOL
entries: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.

name: WYNAUT
entries: In the snow country, certain folklore says a house will prosper if a SNORUNT lives there.

name: SNORUNT
entries: To protect itself, it clads its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.

name: GLALIE
entries: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.

name: SPHEAL
entries: It habitually spins things on its nose. By doing so, it learns textures and odors.

name: SEALEO
entries: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.

name: WALREIN
entries: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

name: CLAMPERL
entries: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

name: HUNTAIL
entries: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

name: GOREBYSS
entries: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

name: RELICANTH
entries: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

name: LUVDISC
entries: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: BAGON
entries: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

name: SHELGON
entries: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.

name: SALAMENCE
entries: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

name: BELDUM
entries: It is formed by two BELDUM joining together. Its steel body won’t be scratched if it collides with a jet.

name: METANG
entries: METANG combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.

name: METAGROSS
entries: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.

name: REGIROCK
entries: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: REGICE
entries: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

name: REGISTEEL
entries: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

name: LATIAS
entries: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

name: LATIOS
entries: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

name: KYOGRE
entries: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought KYOGRE long ago.

name: GROUDON
entries: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: RAYQUAZA
entries: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

name: JIRACHI
entries: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: DEOXYS
entries: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

name: TURTWIG
entries: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: GROTLE
entries: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

name: TORTERRA
entries: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

name: CHIMCHAR
entries: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

name: MONFERNO
entries: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

name: INFERNAPE
entries: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: PIPLUP
entries: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

name: PRINPLUP
entries: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

name: EMPOLEON
entries: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: STARLY
entries: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

name: STARAVIA
entries: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

name: STARAPTOR
entries: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: BIDOOF
entries: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: BIBAREL
entries: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.

name: KRICKETOT
entries: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

name: KRICKETUNE
entries: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: SHINX
entries: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

name: LUXIO
entries: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

name: LUXRAY
entries: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

name: BUDEW
entries: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

name: ROSERADE
entries: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

name: CRANIDOS
entries: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

name: RAMPARDOS
entries: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

name: SHIELDON
entries: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

name: BASTIODON
entries: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: BURMY
entries: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

name: WORMADAM
entries: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

name: MOTHIM
entries: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.

name: COMBEE
entries: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.

name: VESPIQUEN
entries: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: PACHIRISU
entries: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

name: BUIZEL
entries: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: FLOATZEL
entries: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

name: CHERUBI
entries: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

name: CHERRIM
entries: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

name: SHELLOS
entries: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

name: GASTRODON
entries: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: AMBIPOM
entries: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

name: DRIFLOON
entries: It’s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

name: DRIFBLIM
entries: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

name: BUNEARY
entries: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

name: LOPUNNY
entries: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

name: MISMAGIUS
entries: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.

name: HONCHKROW
entries: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: GLAMEOW
entries: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.

name: PURUGLY
entries: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

name: CHINGLING
entries: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: STUNKY
entries: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

name: SKUNTANK
entries: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

name: BRONZOR
entries: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

name: BRONZONG
entries: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body’s fluid levels by eliminating excess.

name: BONSLY
entries: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

name: MIME JR.
entries: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.

name: HAPPINY
entries: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: CHATOT
entries: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

name: SPIRITOMB
entries: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

name: GIBLE
entries: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

name: GABITE
entries: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

name: GARCHOMP
entries: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

name: MUNCHLAX
entries: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: RIOLU
entries: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

name: LUCARIO
entries: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

name: HIPPOPOTAS
entries: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

name: HIPPOWDON
entries: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

name: SKORUPI
entries: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

name: DRAPION
entries: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

name: CROAGUNK
entries: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: TOXICROAK
entries: It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: CARNIVINE
entries: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: FINNEON
entries: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

name: LUMINEON
entries: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

name: MANTYKE
entries: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

name: SNOVER
entries: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

name: ABOMASNOW
entries: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: WEAVILE
entries: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

name: MAGNEZONE
entries: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: LICKILICKY
entries: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.

name: RHYPERIOR
entries: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: TANGROWTH
entries: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: ELECTIVIRE
entries: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: MAGMORTAR
entries: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

name: TOGEKISS
entries: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: YANMEGA
entries: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: LEAFEON
entries: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

name: GLACEON
entries: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: GLISCOR
entries: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: MAMOSWINE
entries: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: PORYGON-Z
entries: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

name: GALLADE
entries: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

name: PROBOPASS
entries: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: DUSKNOIR
entries: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

name: FROSLASS
entries: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: ROTOM
entries: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: UXIE
entries: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: MESPRIT
entries: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: AZELF
entries: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: DIALGA
entries: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

name: PALKIA
entries: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: HEATRAN
entries: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: REGIGIGAS
entries: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: GIRATINA
entries: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: CRESSELIA
entries: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

name: PHIONE
entries: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: MANAPHY
entries: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: DARKRAI
entries: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

name: SHAYMIN
entries: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.
